Palp as in diagnosis. Embolus arising from tegulum at a 9- to 10-o’clock-position, conductor at a 10- to 11-o’clock-position. Tegulum extending strongly beyond cymbium. Sperm duct running marginally (
Figs 2, 6
).

Colouration. Prosoma orange with small lateral light brown markings. Chelicerae orange with light brown markings. Gnathocoxae pale yellow, distally cream coloured. Labium orange, slightly darker at base. Legs and pedipalps pale orange with small light brown markings and dark brown spots at the base of the spines. Opisthosoma cream coloured with scattered small white markings (
Fig. 74
).

Female (
